  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain sectors are typically required to report suspicious transactions or activities to the appropriate authorities. Specific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Identifying and verifying customer identities\n3. Maintaining transaction records\n4. Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n5. Training staff to recognize suspicious activities\n\nHowever, I want to be clear that I can provide general information about this topic, but I cannot give specific legal advice.",
